value.value: The directed movement of fructose substance from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.
The process in which a manganese ion is transported across a mitochondrial membrane, into or out of the mitochondrion.
The process in which a solute is transported from one side of a membrane to the other into, out of or within a mitochondrion.
The process in which S-adenosyl-L-methionine is transported across a mitochondrial membrane, into or out of the mitochondrion.
The process in which ATP is transported across a mitochondrial membrane, into or out of the mitochondrion.
The process in which thiamine pyrophosphate is transported across a mitochondrial membrane, into or out of the mitochondrion.
The process in which a tricarboxylic acid is transported across a mitochondrial membrane, into or out of the mitochondrion.
The process in which a phosphate ion is transported across a mitochondrial membrane, into or out of the mitochondrion.
The process in which FAD is transported across a mitochondrial membrane, into or out of the mitochondrion.
The process in which NAD is transported across a mitochondrial membrane, into or out of the mitochondrion.
The process in which alpha-ketoglutarate is transported across a mitochondrial membrane, into or out of the mitochondrion.
The process in which 2-oxoadipate is transported across a mitochondrial membrane, into or out of the mitochondrion.
The process in which 5'-adenylyl sulfate is transported across a mitochondrial membrane, into or out of the mitochondrion.
The process in which 3'-phospho-5'-adenylyl sulfate is transported across a mitochondrial membrane, into or out of the mitochondrion.
The process in which oxaloacetate is transported across a mitochondrial membrane, into or out of the mitochondrion.
The process in which 2-isopropylmalate(2-) is transported across a mitochondrial membrane, into or out of the mitochondrion.
The process in which sulfate is transported across a mitochondrial membrane, into or out of the mitochondrion.
The process in which malonate(1-) is transported across a mitochondrial membrane, into or out of the mitochondrion.
The process in which coenzyme A is transported across a mitochondrial membrane, into or out of the mitochondrion.
An exosome complex that is assembled in the multivesicular body (MVB) membrane and chaperoned to the exosome by the ESCRT-III machinery.

definition.value: An example of this is SCD1 in human (UniProt symbol P18827) in PMID:22660413 (inferred from physical interaction).

value.value: A protein complex that is wholly or partially contained within the lumen or membrane of the extracellular vesicular exosome.

definition.value: An example of this is SCD1 in human (UniProt symbol P18827) in PMID:22660413 (inferred from physical interaction).

value.value: Covalent attachment of the ubiquitin-like protein UFM1 to a protein, forming an UFM1 chain.

A protein kinase chaperone complex required for the proper folding, maturation and stabilization of target proteins (mostly signaling protein kinases, some steroid hormone receptors), usually during or immediately after completion of translation. The highly conserved, phosphorylated CDC37-Ser13 (vertebrates) or cdc37-Ser14 (yeast) is essential for complex assembly and target protein binding. CDC37-Ser13 (Ser14) is phosphorylated by Casein kinase II (CK2), which in turn is a target of CDC37 creating a positive feedback loop. Complex binding also prevents rapid ubiquitin-dependent proteosomal degradation of target proteins.

definition.value: An example of this is HSP90AB1 in human (UniProt symbol P08238) in PMID:21855797 (inferred from direct assay).

label.value: I(KACh) inward rectifier potassium channel complex

value.value: An inward rectifier potassium channel complex expressed in cardiac muscle, specifically the sinoatrial node and atria, where it controls the heart rate, via regulation by G protein-coupled receptor signaling. In mammals it is composed of GIRK1 (or Kir3.1) and GIRK4 (or Kir3.4) subunits.

definition.value: Examples of this are KCNJ3 and KCNJ5 in human (Uniprot symbols P48549 and P48544) in PMID:9765280 inferred from orthology sequence evidence.

value.value: A protein serine/threonine phosphatase complex that in S. pombe consists of the proteins Dis2, Ppn1, and Swd22.
The process in which UDP-N-acetylglucosamine is transported across a membrane.
The process in which GDP-mannose is transported across a membrane.
The process by which centromeres/kinetochores attach to and migrate along microtubules to become localized to clusters at the spindle pole body during a meiotic prometaphase I.

A ribonucleoprotein complex that has RNA-directed RNA polymerase (RdRP) activity, and is composed of telomerase reverse transcriptase (TERT) and the non-coding RNA component of mitochondrial RNA processing endoribonuclease (RMRP).

label.value: potassium ion import across plasma membrane

value.value: The directed movement of potassium ions from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.

Any of the meiotic spindle microtubules that radiate in all directions from the spindle poles and are thought to contribute to the forces that separate the poles and position them in relation to the rest of the cell.
The process in which L-ornithine is transported across a mitochondrial membrane, into or out of the mitochondrion.

Combining with an extracellular glucose molecule and transmitting the signal across the membrane by activating an associated G-protein; promotes the exchange of GDP for GTP on the alpha subunit of a heterotrimeric G-protein complex.
The removal of a methyl group from the C-terminal amino acid of a protein.
The membrane of the perinuclear endoplasmic reticulum, which is the portion of endoplasmic reticulum, the intracellular network of tubules and cisternae, that occurs near the nucleus.
The phosphorylation of a peptidyl-serine to form peptidyl-O-phospho-L-serine on an identical protein. For example, phosphorylation by the other kinase within a homodimer.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cytoplasmic translational termination.
Binds to and increases the activity of the enzyme phospholipase D.

A complex of accessory proteins (cardiac troponin T, cardiac troponin I and cardiac troponin C) found associated with actin in cardiac muscle thin filaments; involved in calcium regulation important for muscle contraction.
Catalysis of the reaction: trans-4-hydroxy-L-prolyl-[protein] + UDP-beta-L-arabinofuranose = H+ + O-(beta-L-arabinofuranosyl)-trans-4-hydroxy-L-prolyl-[protein] + UDP.

A protein complex required for prokaryotic cell division (FtsZ-dependent cytokinesis). These complexes are assembled and recruited to the cell septum in a strictly controlled sequence and co-ordinate invagination of the cell membrane, inward growth of the peptidoglycan layer, constriction of the outer membrane and separation of daughter cells.

A protein complex required for prokaryotic cell division (FtsZ-dependent cytokinesis). Part of the divisome. Assembled independently of the other divisome components in the cytoplasm prior to transport to the cell septum. In E. coli consists of FtsB, FtsL and FtsQ.

definition.value: An example of this is FtsB in E. coli (P0A6S5) in PMID:15165235 (inferred from physical interaction).

value.value: A protein complex required for prokaryotic cell division (FtsZ-dependent cytokinesis). Part of the divisome. Assembled independently of the other divisome components in the cytoplasm prior to transport to the cell septum. In E. coli consists of FtsB and FtsL.

definition.value: An example of this is FtsB in E. coli (P0A6S5) in PMID:15165235 (inferred from physical interaction).

value.value: Transcription factor complex consisting of ATF4 and CREB1 subunits that is capable of binding to cAMP response element (CRE) (consensus: 5'-GTGACGT[AC][AG]-3') as part of the positive regulation of transcription. Regulatory targets include the GRP78 (HSPA5) promoter in humans, whose activation by this complex is part of the ER stress response pathway.

Transcription factor complex consisting of ATF1 and ATF4 subunits that is capable of binding to cAMP response element (CRE) (consensus: 5'-GTGACGT[AC][AG]-3') of the GRP78 (HSPA5) promoter. Involved in the ER stress response pathway.

definition.value: An example of this is ATF1in human (P18846) in PMID:12871976 (inferred from physical interaction).

value.value: The directed movement of asparagine into the vacuole across the vacuolar membrane.
A protein ufmylation process in which a polymer of the ubiquitin-like protein UFM1 is formed by linkages between lysine residues at position 69 of the UFM1 monomers, is added to a protein.

Binding to nascent polypeptide-associated complex, a heterodimeric protein complex that can reversibly bind to ribosomes and is located in direct proximity to newly synthesized polypeptide chains as they emerge from the ribosome.
Catalysis of the reaction: L-altrarate = 5-dehydro-4-deoxy-D-glucarate + H2O.
Combining with basic secretagogues to initiate pseudo-allergic reactions in mast cells.
